  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0d9f\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca \u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca\u0dc4\u0dbd\u0dca 200\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d85\u0dc0\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca \u0dad\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dba\u0d9a",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "200 garment factories at risk",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is reported that about 200 small and medium scale garment factories are at serious risk of collapse due to problems including fuel shortage and electricity cuts.",
        "Although large-scale garment factories buy diesel from Cipetco and IOC gas stations for dollars, small- and medium-sized garment factories face serious difficulties in obtaining fuel from conventional gas stations.",
        "Also, the workers of the garment factories have lost the opportunity to come by their vehicles due to the lack of fuel, which has greatly affected the performance of the garment factories, the factory owners say.",
        "Large-scale industry has also been affected by the inactivity of large-scale garment factories, which hand over a portion of their garment production orders to small and medium-sized garment factories as subcontractors for production."
      ],
